The paper discusses the use of the Dempster-Shafer model in handling default reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the issue of unacceptable conclusions, which is relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The transferable belief model, which is the focus of the paper, involves the use of probability theory and information theory, making it relevant to the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
